Johns Hopkins, Notre Dame, Duke Win in NCAA’s Lacrosse Tournament Openers

-- B y   M a s o n   L e v i n s o n
-- 
2011-05-15T04:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-14/johns-hopkins-notre-dame-win-ncaa-lacrosse-tournament-openers.html
Cornell University  was an opening-day
winner in the National Collegiate Athletic Association men’s
lacrosse tournament as all four seeded teams won their games.  Second-seeded Cornell beat Hartford 12-5 in Ithaca, New
York; third-seeded  Johns Hopkins  topped Hofstra University 12-5
in Baltimore; No. 4 seed  Notre Dame  beat the University of
Pennsylvania 13-6 in  South Bend ,  Indiana ; and fifth-seeded Duke
won 15-14 over  Delaware  in Durham,  North Carolina . All four
moved into the quarterfinals.  Top seed Syracuse will take on Siena today at home to open
their tournament, while sixth-seeded Denver plays Villanova in
Denver, No. 7  Virginia  hosts Bucknell in Charlottesville,
Virginia, and eighth-seeded North Carolina takes on  Maryland  in
 Chapel Hill , North Carolina.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mason Levinson in  New York  at 
 mlevinson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net . 